{{Han etym}}
''{{w|Shuowen}}'' interprets it to be a {{Han compound|吅|獄|c1=s|c2=p|t1=to speak loudly|ls=psc|nocap=1}}, simplified to {{zh-l|*犬}}.

Alternatively, it may be an {{Han compound|吅|犬|t1=to speak loudly|t2=dog|ls=ic|nocap=1}} – a dog's bark > cry; weep.

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*kuːk||to weep; to wail}}; cognate with {{cog|lus|kûk||to shriek}} (STEDT).

This seems to be an area word; compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*kuk|*kuk ~ kuuk ~ kuək ~ kək|to call}}, {{cog|map-pro|*-kuk||sound of a sob}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

